text: Unleash your imagination and create the residence you've always dreamed of on this expansive 3.6-acre parcel. Offering seclusion and nature's charm, this lot features a beautiful seasonal creek with a picturesque backdrop. Shielded by an array of trees, the property promises a haven of privacy for your future home. Accessibility to utilities is convenient, with water options including the installation of a cistern or establishing a connection from Fruitdale Road, located 500 feet away. Electricity is readily available on-site, easing the initial stages of development. Minutes to town and no HOA - this is the perfect open canvas to bring to life a vision that bespeaks your style and preference.

Nestled on the hill in Mount Vernon, this legacy home offers an unparalleled blend of elegance & comfort. The level oversized double lot is fully fenced, featuring a meticulously landscaped yard that will leave you in awe. The main floor boasts convenient living with a primary suite w/bath off the master. The updated kitchen is a chef's dream, featuring an abundance of cabinetry, modern appliances & inviting sunroom, bathed in natural light. Upstairs, you'll find three generously sized bedrooms, two of which have 3/4 baths, plus plus an additional full bath. The finished basement is a versatile space with a home office, family room, extra bedroom, 3/4 bath & utility room. This home is brimming with special features & timeless charm.

Nestled in the heart of the Pacific Northwest, this 40-acre vacant land listing in Sedro Wolley, WA, offers a unique opportunity for those seeking privacy, seclusion, and natural beauty. W/ its lush greenery and territorial views, this property is the perfect canvas for your dream home or development project. W/ easy access to major highways, schools, and shopping, this lot offers seclusion and convenience. Whether you're an investor, developer, or homeowner, this property is an excellent investment opportunity with much potential. Imagine waking up to the stunning Pacific Northwest landscape every morning. This 40-acre lot provides ample space for a custom-built home or possible subdividing and development. Currently in Forestry Zoning

Experience breathtaking views of Mt. Baker and Fidalgo Bay from this sunlit haven. Revel in the warmth of natural light dancing on beautiful hardwood floors throughout. With spacious living areas and a sizable bonus room upstairs, there's ample space for all your needs. Two primary suites, each on its own level, offer unparalleled convenience and privacy. Need to work from home? Enjoy the dedicated office space on the main floor. Step outside to unwind on the back deck or patio, nestled within a fully fenced backyard adorned with lush landscaping. Perfectly situated near town amenities and parks, this home offers both tranquility and convenience in one unbeatable package.

Embrace majestic mountain views, 9+ acres, all things outdoor enthusiasts crave! This 1959 built, 2 bd + bonus room, 3/4 bth home is on the cusp of being glorious once again with your vision. Featuring 1-level living, era-essential built-ins, comfortable living room w/ free-standing wood stove, large picture window frames the idyllic view, dining room, utility room, 2 bedrooms + bonus room w/closet that could easily be converted into a bedroom or remain an office/hobby room, a Generac generator for peace of mind. Full unfinished basement ideal for storage, transforming into a shop/hobby space. Nestled in the Birdsview area, approx. 2 miles to Rasar State Park, and a stone's throw to all the gorgeous scenery/activities the PNW has to offer!

Step into seaside living at this Skyline area condo with abundant storage. The main level offers a perfect view of the grassy park near the tennis courts. The spacious master suite is conveniently situated on the main level, while the lower level features a family room, full bath, two large bedrooms and extra storage. With an attached 2-car garage, you'll enjoy added privacy and security. You'll have the freedom to maintain your own yard and exterior and enjoy the outdoor living space(s) including a large deck. This meticulously maintained unit comes fully equipped with all appliances, including a washer and dryer.

Terrific Anacortes home in a fantastic location!! This 1800 sqft+ 3 bedroom 2.5 house features main floor living on a huge corner landscaped lot just minutes to town. The main floor features a huge kitchen with tons of light, large dining area, living room, den, nice utility room, a powder room and master bedroom with a private bath. The upper floor has two huge bedrooms and full bath. Nice sized garage with a fantastic loft for storage too. Don't miss out on this wonderful opportunity to live in a great Anacortes neighborhood!!

Guemes Island, beach front cabin just an 8 minute ferry ride from Anacortes. Low bank waterfront home with amazing views of islands and beautiful Mt Baker on this cozy, friendly island. Bring your imagination and make this cabin, your own. Complete with 3 bedrooms, 3/4 bath, woodstove, spacious deck, community well with good, reliable water. Two buoy moorings are in place just waiting for the buoys to tie up your boat. Just imagine kayaking from your own beach, beach combing, crabbing and low tides that makes for amazing clam digging or just sit and enjoy! Guemes Island General Store offers fun summer time evening entertainment with a view & very tasty dining.

text: Welcome to Brickyard Park a 55+ community! This COMPLETED home is a 2 bed +Den 1.75 attached rambler unit. It has an open concept great room w/a gas fireplace. There are over $29K in upgrades in this home. Kitchen w/gas range and upgraded quartz countertops throughout the home. LVP flooring & upgraded carpet. Heat pump w/mini splits for heat/AC. The bathrooms & garage are insulated. ADA height toilets in both baths. Primary ensuite has walk in closets. There are solatubes throughout the home for extra light. 2 car garage. Community clubhouse has an acre park w/a walking trail around it. There is a pickleball court, horseshoe pits & area for lawn games. Covered rear patio. Pics are of a different home, features, colors may differ.

VIEWS VIEWS VIEWS! Here you will find the intersection of highbank waterfront, elegance, modern amenities, and affordability. Built in 2020 for comfort, convenience, and low maintenance with LVP flooring, quartz counters, composite decking, tankless water heater, and a heat pump w/ A/C for energy efficiency. Custom cabinets, heated primary bathroom floor, soaking tub, custom window treatments, and one of a kind stained glass entry door created by a local artist round out the perfect island beach home package. The shed can be utilized as a hobby space, or for additional storage. Enjoy private community beach access from one of the three beaches (Cooks Cove w/ boat ramp, Long Bay, or Deadman's Cove.) You don't want to miss this one!

text: Rarely available beach home in coveted Madrona Estates, located on Cypress Island. Perched on a bluff overlooking Strawberry Bay, the Southwest facing views of the Sound are framed by the magnificent backdrop of sunsets over the Olympic Mountains. Cypress Islands vast trail system stretches 5100 acres of remote DNR land, enjoy hiking in solitude right out your back door. Access over 800 feet of the community beach for kayaking, fishing, camp fires with Smores or maybe just searching for beach glass. Unwind on this turnkey property, complete with new solar system (panels/batteries), interior/exterior paint, 50-year metal roof, flooring, and so much more.

Enjoy sunset views across the water watching boats sail by, eagles soaring, cute otters frolicking & seals peering at you! Patio on waterside w/firepit & views of Mt Baker for entertaining & relaxing. New: luxury vinyl plank floors, heaters in bdrms, & fans in bthrms. Floor/ceiling stone wall w/gas fireplace, vaulted ceilings w/ beams. Updated 2-3/4 baths. 692 sq ft Bonus Room (prev used as studio) built over old pool w/separate entrance, storage underneath, sink, gas fireplace and a view down the Channel. Could us as office, craft room, or primary bdrm w/ bthrm attached. Newer 10x16 Heritage outbuilding w/sliding glass door. HOA Community access to beach, boat ramp & RV storage. 7 min to Hwy 20. Fee Simple land. 1 yr HOME WARRANTY.

Where elegance meets island charm! Walls of windows & doors frame nearly 180-degree views from almost every room in this custom Guemes Island home. Talk about location! A stones throw from ferry dock & General Store. 5-min ferry to Old Towns restaurants, shops & marinas. Set on one acre, you have main floor living w/3 beds & den; spacious great room w/fireplace & built-ins, French doors w/stained glass transom lead to ensuite primary. Farmhouse kitchen w/multi-hued surfaces, plank flooring, banquette seating & granite island, a corner kitchen window looks east at Deadmans Bay & Cascades. To west & south, boat traffic of all shapes & sizes. Covered wrap-around deck w/hot tub for year-round fun. Also for sale 4.5 acres MLS 2231518.
